===Etymology===
Related to rGyalrongic cognates like {{cog|sit-jap|tɯɣmɯr|tɯ-ɣmɯr|t=night}} and {{cog|sit-sit|təmōr|tə-mōr|t=night}} ({{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques & Lai 2019}}). From this, one can reconstruct {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mor}}.

For the term meaning both “evening” and “late”, compare typologically {{m+|mn|орой}}, {{m+|es|tarde}}, {{m+|la|sērōtinus}}. Also compare {{m+|it|sera}}, {{m+|fr|soir}} (< {{m+|la|sērus}}).

